    { id: 803, question: "Assertion (A): A mango seed will germinate to form a mango tree. Reason (R): Heredity determines the process by which traits and characteristics are reliably inherited from parents to offspring.", options: ["Both A and R are true, and R is the correct explanation of A.", "Both A and R are true, but R is not the correct explanation of A.", "A is true, but R is false.", "A is false, but R is true."], correctAnswer: "Both A and R are true, and R is the correct explanation of A.", marks: 1, year: "2025" },
    { id: 804, question: "When a pure-tall pea plant is crossed with a pure-dwarf pea plant, the percentage of tall pea plants in F1 and F2 generation pea plants will be respectively:", options: ["100%; 25%", "100%; 50%", "100%; 75%", "100%; 100%"], correctAnswer: "100%; 75%", marks: 1, year: "2025" },
    { id: 805, question: "A tall pea plant with round seeds (TTRR) is crossed with a short pea plant with wrinkled seeds (ttrr). The F₁ generation will be:", options: ["25% tall with round seeds", "50% tall with wrinkled seeds", "75% tall with wrinkled seeds", "100% tall with round seeds"], correctAnswer: "100% tall with round seeds", marks: 1, year: "2025" },
    { id: 806, question: "Mendel obtained F₂ generation by:", options: ["Self-pollinating F₁ generation plants", "Cross-pollinating F₁ generation plants with plants having dominant trait", "Cross-pollinating F₁ generation plants with plants having recessive trait", "Cross-pollinating both the parents"], correctAnswer: "Self-pollinating F₁ generation plants", marks: 1, year: "2025" },
    { id: 807, question: "Consider the following statements: (i) The sex of a child is determined by what it inherits from the mother. (ii) The sex of a child is determined by what it inherits from the father. (iii) The probability of having a male child is more than that of a female child. (iv) The sex of a child is determined at the time of fertilisation when male and female gametes fuse to form a zygote.", options: ["(i) and (iii)", "(ii) and (iv)", "(iii) and (iv)", "(i), (iii) and (iv)"], correctAnswer: "(ii) and (iv)", marks: 1, year: "2024" },
    { id: 808, question: "Assertion (A): Human female has a perfect pair of sex chromosomes. Reason (R): Sex chromosome contributed by the human male in the zygote decides the sex of a child.", options: ["Both (A) and (R) are true and (R) is the correct explanation of (A).", "Both (A) and (R) are true, but (R) is not the correct explanation of (A).", "(A) is true, but (R) is false.", "(A) is false, but (R) is true."], correctAnswer: "Both (A) and (R) are true, but (R) is not the correct explanation of (A).", marks: 1, year: "2024" },
    { id: 809, question: "In an experiment to study independent inheritance of two separate traits: shape and colour of seeds, the ratio of the different combinations in F₂ progeny would be", options: ["1 : 3", "1 : 2 : 1", "9 : 3 : 3 : 1", "9 : 1 : 1 : 3"], correctAnswer: "9 : 3 : 3 : 1", marks: 1, year: "2024" },
    { id: 810, question: "A cross made between two pea plants produces 50% tall and 50% short pea plants. The gene combination of the parental pea plants must be", options: ["Tt and Tt", "TT and Tt", "Tt and tt", "TT and tt"], correctAnswer: "Tt and tt", marks: 1, year: "2024" },
    { id: 811, question: "A cross between two tall pea plants resulted in offspring having a few dwarf plants. The gene-combination of the parental plants must be", options: ["Tt and Tt", "Tt and tt", "TT and tt", "TT and Tt"], correctAnswer: "Tt and Tt", marks: 1, year: "2024" },
    { id: 812, question: "A cross between pea plant with white flowers (w) and pea plant with violet flowers (VV) resulted in F₂ progeny in which ratio of violet (VV) and white (w) flowers will be", options: ["1 : 1", "2 : 1", "3 : 1", "1 : 3"], correctAnswer: "3 : 1", marks: 1, year: "2023" },
    { id: 813, question: "Assertion (A): In humans, if gene (B) is responsible for black eyes and gene (b) is responsible for brown eyes, then the colour of eyes of the progeny having gene combination bb or Bb will be black only. Reason (R): The black colour of the eyes is a dominant trait.", options: ["Both (A) and (R) are true and (R) is the correct explanation of (A).", "Both (A) and (R) are true and (R) is not the correct explanation of (A).", "(A) is true but (R) is false.", "(A) is false but (R) is true."], correctAnswer: "(A) is false but (R) is true.", marks: 1, year: "2023" },
    { id: 814, question: "Consider the following two statements: (i) The trait that expresses itself in the F1 gene. (ii) The trait that keeps on passing from one generation to another. The appropriate terms for the statements (i) and (ii) respectively are", options: ["Recessive trait; Dominant trait", "Dominant trait; Recessive trait", "Dominant trait; Inherited trait", "Recessive trait; Inherited trait"], correctAnswer: "Dominant trait; Inherited trait", marks: 1, year: "2023" },
    { id: 815, question: "Assertion (A): Human population shows a great deal of variations in traits. Reason (R): All variations in a species have equal chances of surviving in the environment in which they live.", options: ["Both Assertion (A) and Reason (R) are true and Reason (R) is the correct explanation of the Assertion (A)", "Both Assertion (A) and Reason (R) are true, but Reason (R) is not the correct explanation of the Assertion (A)", "Assertion (A) is true, but Reason (R) is False.", "Assertion (A) is false, but Reason (R) is true"], correctAnswer: "Assertion (A) is true, but Reason (R) is False.", marks: 1, year: "2023" },
    { id: 816, question: "The statement that correctly describes the characteristic(s) of a gene is:", options: ["In individuals of a given species, a specific gene is located on a particular chromosome.", "A gene is not the information source for making proteins in the cell.", "Each chromosome has only one gene located all along its length.", "All the inherited traits in human beings are not controlled by genes."], correctAnswer: "In individuals of a given species, a specific gene is located on a particular chromosome.", marks: 1, year: "2023" },
    { id: 817, question: "Assertion (A): Genes inherited from the parents decide the sex of a child. Reason (R): X chromosome in a male child is inherited from his father.", options: ["Both (A) and (R) are true and (R) is the correct explanation of (A).", "Both (A) and (R) are true and (R) is not the correct explanation of (A).", "(A) is true but (R) is false.", "(A) is false but (R) is true.", "Both (A) and (R) are false."], correctAnswer: "Both (A) and (R) are false.", marks: 1, year: "2023" }
